Of the king with his grandees (<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">megistanes</SPAN>). So, on the death of Germanicus, it was said <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">regum etiam regem et exercitatione venandi et convictu megistanum abstinuisse, quod apud Parthos iustiti instar est</SPAN>
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Suetonius/12Caesars/Caligula*.html#5
	"TARGET="Suetonius_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EPlusL,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(Suet. <I>Cal.</I> 5)</A>.<A CLASS="correction"
onMouseOver="return Ebox('The printed edition<BR>has '+BadF+'7'+CloseF+'',WIDTH,120)"
onMouseOut="nd();">º</A>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note8" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Tacitus/Annals/2A*.html#ref8
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">8</A>
Artabanus III (11‑40 <SPAN CLASS="small">A.D.</SPAN>).


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note9" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Tacitus/Annals/2A*.html#ref9
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">9</A>
A Scythian race to the south-east of the Caspian Sea.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note10" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Tacitus/Annals/2A*.html#ref10
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">10</A>
The following list of Armenian sovereigns may make this and the following chapter a little clearer: 56 or 55 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>‑34 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN> <I>Artavasdes I</I> (played Antony false in his Parthian campaign of 36 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>; entrapped by him two years later and handed to Cleopatra; executed by her in 30 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>): 33 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>‑<A ID="p387x"></A>20 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN> <I>Artaxias II</I> ("<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">nobis infensus</SPAN>"; massacred all Romans in his dominions): 20 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>‑6 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>, approximately, <I>a.</I> <I>Tigranes II</I> ("<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">datus a Caesare Armeniis</SPAN>"; established on the throne by Tiberius — see
	<A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/horace/epist1.shtml
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(EClickHere+'Horace\'s Epistles, Book 1'+Lat2+LatSearch+'Armenius</SPAN>',WIDTH,185)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Hor. <I>Epp.</I> <SPAN CLASS="small">I</SPAN>.12.26</A>);<A CLASS="correction"
onMouseOver="return Ebox('The Loeb edition —<BR>thru nnn years of reprintings! —<BR>has '+SearchF+'12.'+CloseF+''+BadF+'1'+CloseF+''+SearchF+'6'+CloseF+'',WIDTH,120)"
onMouseOut="nd();">º</A> <I>b. Tigranes III</I> and <I>Erato</I> (husband and wife as well as brother and sister; joint sovereigns); 6 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>‑1 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>, approximately, <I>a. Artavasdes II</I> ("<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">iussu Augusti impositus</SPAN>"); <I>b. Tigranes III</I> and <I>Erato</I>


<A ID="p388x"></A>(restored): 1 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>‑11 <SPAN CLASS="small">A.D.</SPAN>, approximately, <I>a. Ariobarzanes</I> ("<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">origine Medus</SPAN>"); <I>b. Artavasdes III</I> (his son); <I>c. Tigranes IV</I> (<I>cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Tacitus/Annals/6B*.html#40
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();"><SPAN CLASS="small">VI</SPAN>.40</A>); <I>d. Erato</I> (again restored?): 11 or 12 <SPAN CLASS="small">A.D.</SPAN> <I>Vonones</I>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note11" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Tacitus/Annals/2A*.html#ref11
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">11</A>
The allusion, of course, is to the custom of sister-marriage — the survival probably of a period when the blood royal could be transmitted only in the female line. Familiar instances are the Carian dynasties (Mausolus-Artemisia, Idrieus-Ada) and the native and even Ptolemaic sovereigns of Egypt (Ptolemy Philadelphius-Arsinoë, Ptolemy Philopator-Arsinoë).


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note12" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Tacitus/Annals/2A*.html#ref12
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">12</A>
See
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Tacitus/Annals/1A*.html#3
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<SPAN CLASS="small">I</SPAN>.3</A>. Invested with proconsular power and sent out as vice-regent to the eastern provinces in 1 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>, he was treacherously wounded in Armenia (3 <SPAN CLASS="small">A.D.</SPAN>), and died before reaching Italy (Feb. 21, 4 <SPAN CLASS="small">A.D.</SPAN>).


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note13" HREF="
